      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Bebe Miles was a well-known gardener from Pennsylvania. She was the author of several books
            on gardening and natural materials. She died in 1980. [Source: <extref href="http://americanvioletsociety.org/Books_N_Articles/Review_Bebe.htm">Book review
               by Norma Beredjiklian, July 2000</extref>] </p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The<emph render="bold"> Bebe Miles Manuscript</emph> consists of writings. </p>
         <p><emph render="bold">Writings</emph> consist of material used in the development of
            Miles' book, <emph render="italic">The Wonderful World of Bulbs</emph>. Materials
            include a tentative outline, early chapter drafts, a first draft, a carbon copy of the
            first draft, a galley proof, color page proofs, and a bibliography in the form of index
            cards. The book was published in 1963, so this material obviously predates the book's
            publication.</p>
      </scopecontent>
